At 3-month follow-up, we will conduct in-person debriefing interviews with 20 participants assigned to the C2C condition to obtain data on its feasibility, acceptability, and perceived efficacy (including reasons C2C is or is not helpful). Interviews will be audiotaped and transcribed to facilitate analysis. Participants will be compensated for completion of the interview. Patients who receive < 3 C2C sessions (n = 14; 7 at each site) and patients who receive \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
